 directing his own films, beginning with “Fun Radio” in 1963.\nAfter the success of his film \"Rise and Fall of Squizzy Taylor\"  he began teaching at the Swinburne University of Technology (1970-1984)  while continuing to make films on a diverse range of subjects. \nHe was also a co-founder and the artistic director of the St Kilda Film Festival from 1986 to 1990.Buesst has been described as \"a living legend of Melbourne's film scene\"  and was a figure in the \"Carlton wave\" of Australian filmmaking.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-09-05T23:31:21.933270+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 4781, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nigel_Buesst"}], "uuid": "4eb9912d-f265-4139-9a1a-8efb84203304", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "111523", "external_references": [{"id": 25402, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q16104830"}, {"id": 30528, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "27147094990625080104"}, {"id": 30529, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "viaf-27147094990625080104"}], "date_modified": "2025-03-12T00:09:14.705239+11:00"}, {"id": 8740, "name": "Karly Fontaine", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2633067, "title": "Self construct", "work_id": 114095, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-08-11T12:51:58.018962+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "b340468e-bc8a-4223-b7f0-e7f2afda6ae4", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "111707", "external_references": [], "date_modified": "2025-02-28T22:40:54.604624+11:00"}, {"id": 8738, "name": "Hans Breder", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2633050, "title": "The Nazi loop", "work_id": 108660, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_pr